1,000pp a day quadding those wyvern for hides, gems, and misc vendor trash.  So I have the same question everyone else has.  Whats next?<br>
<br>
I have quadded raptors and the xp is better but the loots are non existent.  Where can I go to get at least decent xp AND decent cash at the same time?<br>
<br>
<br>
V <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=656028"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/2003/04/18/flamingtext_com_1050702258_30017.gif" style="border:0;"alt="V"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=656053"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/2003/04/18/flamingtext_com_1050703774_23380.gif" style="border:0;"alt="Angel"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuuk01>Nuuk01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 7:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 58th and needs money</span><hr size=1> <br>
IMO at level 58 there are few better spots for GREAT CASH and DECENT XP than quadding the sentient suits in WL.<br>
<br>
There's a few threads here that I've chimed in about them but I'll give you the run down.<br>
<br>
Along the northern wall of the zone there's 2 camps of Sentient Suits of Armor. They are big animated suits that hit hard with a fair amount of hp. I was easily able to kill them at 57 but KEI and mage earring help a LOT.<br>
<br>
One of the camps has a 4 spawn (how perfect) but I found only one real easy way to pull all of them nicely bunched without running around the building 16 times. I would invis up WITH SKIN ON....go to the back 2 spawns....click off invis and run out the hut.....you will get attacked....you will usually take a little bit of damage.....I only died once or twice in all of level 57 and 58 and half of 59.<br>
<br>
It will take you a few days to learn the paths through the trees that you are comfortable with. My suggestion is run these first 4 straight out towards Kael (zig zag a little to bunch them up better) and snare there. You can run forward for one pillar then turn around and you have the best runway for pulling them back towards camp. Run backwards if you have to but DON'T RUN THEM IN TO TREES. It will screw up your bunch. I ran backwards more than forwards there for a while.<br>
<br>
Adds- you'll get the occasional panther add. Root it...snare it...and eeal with it after. they die in 3 draughts. The good thing is that the panther skins sell for 100p in bazaar. Holgresh are just a nusence. You'll resist all their spells.<br>
<br>
The other camp is very much the same. There's a 4 spawn and a 2 spawn attached. just pull those 4 the same way. These you'll have to run uphill to the left and then to the right when it levels off. Snare when appropraite and run them towards the same spot you killed the first 4.<br>
<br>
Loot- they drop cash gems and Sentient Armor and the good quest gems. Crushed topaz and crushed flame emerald can sell for 1k each.<br>
<br>
I made good xp and a lot of money at this camp.<br>
<br>
when you get to 59 try to do Geonids. very fun and good camp but I'll save you the details of that camp until you get to 59 =)<br>
<br>
Nuuk Sfortenk<br>
63 Wizard of Quellious<br>
