<br>
Standing up along the zone wall looking downslope at the four spawn you should be able to position youself where you see one suit's head and upper body sticking above the notch in the little roofless fort.  Target him and go straight down towards the hut and him.  Right when yu get to a few feet from the fort, take a hard turn to the left and immediately flux the suit.  Run parallel to but a little ways out from the fort and you should get all four of the suits after you.  <br>
<br>
This techinique gets all four most of the time if you time your flux correctly.  If any suit gets left behind it is usually only one in the back of the fort and you can turn around and head back for him and flux him no prob.<br>
<br>
However I like doing the suits as well and your technique, though crazy sounding, intrigues me somewhat.  Maybe I will skin up and give it a try. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 3:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 58th and needs money</span><hr size=1> If you have decent resists or your epic you can go to arcyla ruins and take things at the zonein, its root bombin vs blue casters, in about one hour it netted me 1k, split amongs 4 that were there but i have no doubt i could have soloed it with skins. adds tend to stand and nuke away so if your resists are ok you can laugh as you burn them a new one.<br>
<br>
Drops are reserch every now and then, grimling toes, the runes that are not for reserch (stackable and can go for up to 8pp) and acryla both normal and black. sells nicly dungeon exp is ok, but grab a semi healer (druid shamy ranger pally necro) all work well.<br>
