<br>
1) Use Pillar of Lighting, not Pillar of Flame.  They're fairly fire resistant, but hardly resist magic at all.  This was very painful knowlege to come by.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) Until you learn the terrain well, I'd suggest taking out the troll mercenaries north of the eastern suit camp before starting on the suits.  They're easy if you get them alone, but they can cause real trouble if they add while you're quadding suits.  They're fairly magic-resistant, so the first snare won't always get all three. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
